FBIS4-30965 "dreeu106_i_94009" FBIS-EEU-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Abdic Delivers Address on Private Radio Station Abdic Delivers Address on Private Radio Station AU0106151094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 1 Jun 94 AU0106151094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Our correspondent Mirza Sadikovic reports from the Bihac Region that members of the (?Kladusa) and [word indistinct] paramilitary are much more active at this moment. [Begin Sadikovic recording] Along with their standard activity with infantry, antitank, and antiaircraft weapons, they also continued their crimes against the local population whom they are still pushing into conflict. This is particularly intensive in the regions of (Pecigrad), Todorovo, [name indistinct], and Sturlic. Robbery and (?even) rapes are basic crimes they are committing against civilians. The fact that many things are [word indistinct] in Velika Kladusa is shown by last night's address by the self-proclaimed [word indistinct] Abdic via his private Radio Velkaton Station. In his usual hostile way, he (?criticized) the people. He complained that he does not have enough money, that [word indistinct] cannot live off his Agrokomerc Combine, and the like. He demanded a more energetic struggle even after he [words indistinct]. [end recording]
